The following provisions shall apply and have effect in relation to every referendum petition presented by a person other than the Attorney-General, that is to say:
(a) where there are two or more petitioners and one or more but not all of them dies or die at any time before the final order of the court on the trial of the petition, the surviving petitioner or petitioners shall be entitled to carry on the petition subject to such application or order as may be required by rules made under section seventeen;
where there are two or more petitioners and one or more but not all of them dies or die at any time before the final order of the court on the trial of the petition, the surviving petitioner or petitioners shall be entitled to carry on the petition subject to such application or order as may be required by rules made under section seventeen;
(b) where the only or the last surviving petitioner dies at any time before the final order of the court on the trial of the petition, the High Court shall, on the application of the Attorney-General, transfer the carriage of the petition to the Attorney-General and thereupon all subsequent proceedings on the petition shall be conducted as if the petition were a petition presented by the Attorney-General;
