(c) if the petitioner fails to proceed with reasonable speed with the proceedings on the petition, the High Court may, on the application of the Attorney-General, either forthwith make a final order confirming without alteration the declared result to which the petition relates or transfer the carriage of the petition to the Attorney-General and authorise him to proceed on the petition as if it had been presented by him;
